    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is structured as a navigable web application based on the "business-plan-visualized-jp-corrected" report. A fixed sidebar navigation allows users to jump to any of the 7 logical sections instantly. This task-oriented, dashboard-like structure is superior for decision-makers who need to explore specific parts of the business plan (e.g., financials, marketing) without linear scrolling. The content is modularized into cards within each section. This architecture prioritizes user-driven exploration over a passive narrative. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Navigation: A fixed sidebar with active link highlighting (IntersectionObserver) provides clear orientation and non-linear access to all report sections.
        - Layout: A two-column layout (sidebar + main content) creates a classic, user-friendly web application feel.
        - Charts (Bar, Donut, Line, Pie): Used to visualize quantitative data from the report, now placed within cards in their respective sections. The profit forecast chart data is updated to reflect the Japanese plan's figures in JPY. The profit distribution pie chart is correctly implemented to fix the previous runtime error and complete the financial overview.
        - Interactive AI Tools: Placed within their logical sections (Positioning, Blueprint, Area Master Suite, Financials, Roadmap) to allow deep, interactive exploration of the business model's core components, with prompts tailored to the Japanese market context. All JS event listeners now correctly correspond to existing HTML elements.
    -->
